title: For Sale:  WW II Polish P35 Radom 9mm Pistol
postcontent:
This P35 Radom is a "2nd Variant" made 1941-1943 (3 Lever, No Stock Slot - Ser # GXXXX) after the Germans invaded Poland.  The gun was refinished before I bought it with a nice "charcoal blue" very similar to an older Colt blue..  Slide markings are clear, waffenampts are faint but visible, gun has some light pitting in the grooves of the bore.  Light pitting on the front strap and back strap and grip safety show patina. Numbers match on the frame and slide but the barrel is from another gun.

The gun functions perfectly.  I have never had a FTF or FTE with this gun.  Over the 20 years I have owned it I probably put 1000 rds through it.  Accuracy is perfectly acceptable for this type of handgun - 12" plate at 25 yds is easy.

These guns are getting harder to find in any condition, and this is a chance to own an affordable piece of history that you won't be afraid to take to the range and shoot!

FTF at local FFL preferred, will ship for $25 additional.
